SD=Public Reference Data Management
CR=Global Standard Specification
BQs= GlobalReferenceData
This service domain maintains and provides structured access to standard 'global' reference data and definitions associated with market activity such as currency, country and segment identifiers. These values will typically be externally sourced using market information feeds and distributed using whatever is the appropriate mechanism within the bank
The international ISO standard definitions are maintained and applied across production systems of the bank
Provide structured access to standard 'global' reference data and definitions associated with market activity such as currency, country and segment identifiers.
CR - Global Standard Specification							BQ - Global Reference Data	
In	Up	Co	Ec	Ca	Rq	Re	In	Re
InCR Instantiate a new Global Standard Specification
UpCR Update details relating to Global Standard Specification
CoCR Control the processing of Global Standard Specification
EcCR Accept, verify, etc. aspects of Global Standard Specification processing
CaCR Capture Global Standard Specification activity or event related information
RqCR Request manual intervention or a decision with respect to Global Standard Specification
ReCR Retrieve details about any aspect of Global Standard Specification
InBQ Instantiate a new Global Reference Data
ReBQ Retrieve details about any aspect of Global Reference Data